# Example environment variables for contact email delivery

# --- SMTP (nodemailer) - recommended for Gmail App Passwords / simple setup ---
# If you prefer SMTP (Gmail, Sendinblue, Mailgun SMTP, etc.), set these.
# For Gmail: enable 2FA and create an App Password, then set SMTP_USER to your Gmail address and SMTP_PASS to the App Password.

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_SECURE=true
SMTP_USER=your-account@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
SMTP_FROM="CityCare <no-reply@yourdomain.com>"

# --- Optional: SendGrid (API) - alternative to SMTP ---
# If you prefer SendGrid API, set this instead (or in addition).
SENDGRID_API_KEY=your_sendgrid_api_key
SENDGRID_FROM="CityCare <no-reply@yourdomain.com>"

# Recipient that receives contact messages. Defaults to dalmat.repair@gmail.com
CONTACT_RECIPIENT=dalmat.repair@gmail.com

# Notes:
# - For local development, you can copy this file to `.env.local` (if using a local env loader) but DO NOT commit real secrets.
# - On Vercel: go to Project Settings > Environment Variables and add the above keys.
# - On Netlify: go to Site settings > Build & deploy > Environment and add the above keys.
# - Gmail: use an App Password (not your normal account password). See SERVERLESS.md for steps.
